added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds a talent competition to find a superhero worthy of joining the team.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and Robin tries everything to win.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds another talent competition to find the second best superhero team in the world.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and the Titans must find a way to beat the Hive Five.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Justice League Edition Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds yet another talent competition, only this time they're facing off against the Titans.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Justice League Edition Part 2
added.description: In order to be the most talented superhero team in the DC universe, Robin and Beast Boy must work together on a jazz performance.

added.title: More of the Same
added.description: Can the Titans master the four New Year's traditions in order to break the cycle of bad years?

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Ranger Tabes
added.description: To recover a missing package, the Bears get help from Ranger Tabes, an eccentric forest ranger. But her overblown sense of justice might be too much for the Bears to handle.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: The Crew
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin decide it's time they join a crew, they agree that the coolest posse in Elmore is the Senior Citizens. They do everything they can to fit in with them, going to extraordinary lengths to prove themselves worthy of running (well, walking very slowly) with them.

added.title: The Detective
added.description: Anais arrives in the bedroom to find a messy crime-scene and her Daisy doll missing. She realizes Gumball and Darwin are the chief suspects. Following a series of clues is her only chance to track them down and her only hope of learning what happened to Daisy. But as the mystery unravels, it seems the culprits may have turned on each other.

added.title: The Compilation
added.description: A compilation of some of the funniest, most bizarre clips uploaded onto the internet by the people of Elmore. Clips include Banana Joe's self-choreographed acrobatics, Richard's latest culinary invention and Gumball and Darwin's contest for who can pull the weirdest face.

added.title: The Disaster
added.description: When Rob purchases a universal remote from the Awesome Store, he discovers can control the entire universe. He rewinds into the past and remembers Gumball had left him in The Void, leaving him scarred and in his current mutated shape. He uses the universal remote to destroy Gumball's life, whilst Gumball has to figure out what's going on before he's ejected once and for all.

added.title: The Downer
added.description: Gumball is in a funk that is proving hard to shake. Gumball refuses to get out of bed because he is in a lousy mood. When his family try to cheer him up Gumball wishes they'd all just disappear and, inexplicably, they do. At first he enjoys the solitude and doing just as he pleases but soon his mood threatens to take control of him completely.

added.title: The 11th Alien Part 1
added.description: With new Omni-Enhancements in tow, Ben looks to save a town from a sudden mudslide, but his heroics are short lived once Vilgax appears to warn our hero about the consequences of the Omnitrix's mysterious new alien.

added.title: The 11th Alien Part 2
added.description: After discovering that Vilgax has joined forces with the Weatherheads to trick him into turning over the Omnitrix, Ben must not only overcome his doubts, but fully embrace his new powers if he is to beat his foes.

added.title: Bounty Ball
added.description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

added.title: Super-Villain Team-Up
added.description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

added.title: Chicken Nuggets of Wisdom
added.description: When Ben and Max get into an argument, Ben goes Heatblast to blow off steam against Max's wishes; but once Dr. Animo spots him and subsequently turns Max into a chicken, it's up to Ben to right his wrong if he is to save his Grandpa and stop Dr. Animo.

added.title: You're It
added.description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: Ace of Squares
added.description: Craig vows to make the game of Four Square fun again by challenging its most dominant player!

added.title: Big Pinchy
added.description: JP leads his friends on a voyage to find the biggest crayfish in the creek.

added.title: Snots Landing
added.description: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

added.title: Know it All
added.description: Courtney must go all day without correcting her friends which is hard because they do everything wrong!

added.title: A Licking Time Bomb
added.description: Owen and Noah unwittingly become cookie moguls and must hide the secret ingredient, which is Owen's spit from licking the sprinkles off the cookies.

added.title: Election Day
added.description: Apple runs for Mayor.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: The Traveler's Tree
added.description: Guilt-ridden over having lost the Traveler's Tea, Cole embarks on a dangerous quest to the top of a nearby mountain in hopes of finding the legendary Traveler's Tree - a tree which is supposedly guarded by a fearsome beast.

added.title: Krag's Lament
added.description: Cole awakens inside an icy cavern belonging to a legendary beast, and attempts to escape, only to discover a surprising truth.

added.title: Secret of the Wolf
added.description: The Ice Emperor summons an enormous ice Behemoth to attack Lloyd and his faithful wolf companion.

added.title: The Last of the Formlings
added.description: Akita tells the story of the "Choosing" and how she, and her twin brother, Kataru, went into the wilds to discover their animal forms.

added.title: My Enemy, My Friend
added.description: The Ice Emperor's terrible Ice Dragon strikes again, laying waste to the Ice Fisher's village, forcing the ninja to go after Lloyd…

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Cat-Pocalypse
added.description: When Vic gets sick and is stuck in his room, he spies on Pineapple and becomes convinced that Pineapple is creating an army of zombie cats. Val agrees and the two become obsessed with stopping Pineapple before it's too late!

added.title: #FreshPrincessOfRenFaire Part 1
added.description: A fun day at the Renaissance Faire takes a dark turn when our heroes clash with a princess-eating dragon.

added.title: #FreshPrincessOfRenFaire Part 2
added.description: A fun day at the Renaissance Faire takes a dark turn when our heroes clash with a princess-eating dragon.

added.title: ThunderDogs
added.description: The Thundercats agree to foster a demonic puppy from the Astral Plane until they can find it the perfect owner. But could the perfect owner be their worst enemy? Their worst enemy is Mumm-Ra in case you forgot!

added.title: Mini Mongor
added.description: The Thunderkittens unleash a demon who is powered by fear. Too bad he's small and not that scary.

added.title: Swampy Johnny
added.description: The Thundercats invite a super cool swamp man into the Cat's Lair who is on the run from some scary looking aliens!

added.title: Tygra's Garden
added.description: Tygra says he's done being a Thundercat after he gets engaged to a sentient flower. Now it's up to Lion-O to break up the wedding!

added.title: The Space Beam
added.description: The new rulers of Plun-Darr say they'll bring one of the Mutants home; whichever one of them activates a homing beacon that will blow up the Thundercats. Now it's every Mutant for themselves as they battle it out to be the one to activate the beacon!

added.title: Sugar Berry Fever
added.description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.

added.title: Captured Clops
added.description: Badgerclops is tired of his responsibilities at Sheriff's HQ, so he joins the Sky Pirates.

added.title: Flyaway
added.description: When Adorabat's spirit transcends her body during a meditation exercise, Mao Mao and Badgerclops have to figure out a way to return her to the real world.

added.title: Baost in Show
added.description: When Bao Bao returns, and the King makes him his pet, Mao Mao must rescue his ex-partner.

added.title: Fright Wig
added.description: When the King cannot overcome his fears, he abuses having the Sheriff's Dept. on call.

added.title: Beyond the Grotto
added.description: In pursuit of a runaway Sea Lard, Finn and Jake are led down a whirlpool to a curious new land.

added.title: Bonnie & Neddy
added.description: Finn and Jake, acting on orders from Candy Kingdom's new ruler Princess King of Ooo, stumble upon one of the kingdom's greatest secrets.

added.title: Bad Jubies
added.description: There's a catastrophic storm headed for the Grasslands so Finn, LSP and BMO decide to build a bunker for protection, but Jake has plans of his own.

added.title: A King's Ransom
added.description: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

added.title: Crossover
added.description: Prismo needs Finn and Jake's help to stop a catastrophic event from happening somewhere in the multiverse.

added.title: Tooth Trouble
added.description: Puppycorn loses his first tooth and Unikitty's excited for her little bro, now he​ ​gets a visit from​ ​the​ ​legendary Tooth Fairy!​ ​But when the Tooth Fairy is a no-show, Unikitty and her friends take on the mantle and responsibilities. But will they play too fast and loose with loose teeth and hit a raw nerve?

added.title: Camp Unikitty
added.description: The gang's set for an awesome weekend of glamorous, easy-living camping out in fun, friendly nature! But when Hawkodile challenges their idea of camping (it should be a fight for survival in the hostile woods), the gang switch places, with Hawkodile living a luxurious glamp life while Unikitty and the others survive in the wild. Will Unikitty still believe the "great outdoors" are all that great if they meet their doom by natural causes?

added.title: Perfect Moment
added.description: When Hawkodile admits his love for Dr. Fox, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings for her. Unfortunately, Unikitty's grand plans for the perfect moment of love complicates everything.

added.title: Hawkodile Sensei
added.description: On a routine mission, Hawkodile finds some defenseless chipmunks that imprint on him.​ ​The bird bodyguard takes it upon himself to become their Sensei teach the younglings his warrior ways, but Unikitty worries his training is too intense. Will Hawkodile's "all work, no play" lifestyle push the chipmunks too far?

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Firstbourne
added.description: Emperor Garmadon has taken control of Ninjago City where Lloyd retreats to the shadows. Meanwhile, the other Ninja and Young Wu are shipwrecked in the Realm of Oni & Dragon and find they are not alone.

added.title: Primogenita
added.description: El Emperador Garmadon ha tomado el control de Ciudad Ninjago donde Lloyd se retira hacia las sombras. Mientras tanto, los otros Ninjas y Wu Joven quedan varados en el Reino de Oni y Dragón y descubren que no están solos.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Iron & Stone
added.description: Cole and Young Wu attempt to free their friends, who have been taken captive by a tribe of Dragon Hunters. Meanwhile in Ninjago, Lloyd is reunited with some old friends who may prove valuable allies against Emperor Garmadon.

added.title: Hierro y piedra
added.description: Cole y Wu Joven intentan liberar a sus amigos, que han sido capturados por una tribu de Cazadores de Dragones. Mientras tanto en Ninjago, Lloyd se reúne con unos viejos amigos que quizás sean aliados valiosos contra el Emperador Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Radio Free NinjaGo
added.description: Lloyd must find his voice as he leads a small resistance to capture the airwaves in Ninjago City. Meanwhile in the First Realm, Iron Baron takes the Ninja on a dragon hunt.

added.title: Radio Ninjago libre
added.description: Lloyd deberá encontrar su voz mientras lidera una pequeña resistencia para capturar las señales de transmisión en Ciudad Ninjago. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, el Barón de Hierro lleva a los Ninjas en una cacería de dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: How to Build a Dragon
added.description: While Lloyd and the rebels celebrate their successful strike against Emperor Garmadon, in the Realm of Oni and Dragon, the Ninja dare an elaborate escape from the clutches of Iron Baron and his Dragon Hunters.

added.title: Como construir un dragon
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y los rebeldes celebran su exitoso golpe contra el Emperador Garmadon, en el Reino de Oni y Dragón, los Ninjas se aventuran con un elaborado escape de las garras del Barón de Hierro y sus Cazadores de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Gilded Path
added.description: The headquarters to the resistance is breached and Lloyd scrambles to avoid capture. Meanwhile, the Ninja are caught by Heavy Metal, but find an unlikely ally.

added.title: El camino dorado
added.description: El cuartel general de la resistencia es irrumpido y Lloyd lucha por no ser capturado. Mientras tanto, los Ninjas son capturados por Heavy-Metal, pero encuentran un aliado improbable.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Dumptown USA
added.description: Benson is going to fire Mordecai if Rigby can't bring him back from a bizarre land of dudes also known as Dumptown USA.

added.title: Donut Factory Holiday
added.description: The guys have to return a VHS copy of their favorite terrible movie or else pay a huge late fee.

added.title: Gary's Synthesizer
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby unplug some cables in an old synthesizer. They have to travel to the planet of Synthos in order to re-connect them and bring Gary back to life.

added.title: Favorite Shirt
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, and High Five Ghost have to somehow get Muscle Man's favorite shirt back on him before he wakes up.

added.title: Deez Keys
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby need to make a deal with the scientists to get Benson's car keys back.

added.title: Idolo De La Liga De La Justicia: Edicion Del Segundo Mejor Equipo
added.description: La Liga de la Justicia organiza un concurso de talentos para encontrar al segundo mejor equipo de superhéroes.

added.title: Idolo De La Liga De La Justicia P2- Edicion Del Segundo Mejor Equipo
added.description: La competición se intensifica y los Titanes deben encontrar una forma de vencer a la Colmena.

added.title: El Grupo
added.description: Gumball y Darwin intentan unirse a la pandilla de los más malos de la ciudad.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Proximo Idolo de la Liga de la Justicia: Parte 1
added.description: La Liga de la Justicia organiza un concurso de talentos para encontrar a un superhéroe digno de unirse al equipo.

added.title: Proximo Idolo de la Liga de la Justicia: Parte 2
added.description: La competencia se enciende cuando Robin hace lo imposible por ganar.

added.title: Under Wraps
added.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: The Sleeper Part 1
added.description: Despite finding shelter at MacCadam's, Hot Rod is frustrated with their lack of progress rescuing more bots from the Quintesson Loop.

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

added.title: The Sleeper Part 2
added.description: Hot Rod desperately tries to free Optimus from the Loop while Perceptor and Dead End investigate why MacCadam's is hidden from Quintesson attention.

added.title: The Citizen Part 1
added.description: Hot Rod, Clobber, Dead End, and Whirl search the long-buried Titan for MacCadam and anything to help them defeat the Quintessons.

added.title: The Citizen Part 2
added.description: Joined by Perceptor, the ragtag team discover the dormant Titan is far more dangerous than they expected.

added.title: The Trial Part 1
added.description: To awaken the Titan Iaconus, Hot Rod plans a daring rescue of the Autobot's only City Speaker.

added.title: The Trial Part 2
added.description: The botched rescue leaves Hot Rod captured by the Quintessons, and the rest of the team to deal with a new, unwelcome bot sprung from The Loop.

added.title: Watch It!
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Problemas Dentales
added.description: A Puppycorn se le cae su primer diente, y Unikitty está emocionada por su hermanito, ique ahora recibirá la visita de la legendaria Hada de los Dientes! Pero cuando el Hada de los Dientes no aparece, Unikitty y sus amigos asumen la responsabilidad. ¿Acaso se meterán demasiado rápido y con demasiada soltura con los dientes sueltos y tocarán un nervio sensible?

added.title: Campamento Unikitty
added.description: La pandilla está lista para un fin de semana increíble, para vivir la buena vida acampando con estilo en la divertida y amigable naturaleza. Pero cuando Halcondrilo desafía su idea de acampar (debería ser una lucha por la supervivencia en los bosques hostiles), la pandilla intercambia el lugar con él: ahora, Halcondrilo vive una vida de campamento glamoroso mientras Unikitty y los otros sobreviven en la naturaleza. ¿Seguirá creyendo Unikitty que la "increíble naturaleza" es tan increíble si encuentran su destrucción por causas naturales?

added.title: Momento Perfecto
added.description: Cuando Halcondrilo admite su amor por la Dra. Fox, Unikitty y sus amigos se convierten en sus gurús del amor para ayudarlo a confesar sus sentimientos por ella. Por desgracia, los grandes planes de Unikitty para el momento perfecto del amor lo complican todo.

added.title: El Onceavo Alienigena Parte 1
added.description: Con sus nuevas Omni-Mejoras, Ben intenta salvar una ciudad de un repentino alud. Pero su heroísmo dura poco, porque llega Vilgax a advertirlo de las consecuencias del misterioso alien del Omnitrix.

added.title: Sensei Halcondrilo
added.description: En una misión de rutina, Halcondrilo encuentra algunas ardillas indefensas que lo siguen como abrojos. El ave guardaespaldas decide convertirse en Sensei para enseñar a los jóvenes sus destrezas de guerrero. Pero Unikitty teme que su entrenamiento sea demasiado intenso. ¿El estilo de vida de Halcondrilo en el que todo es trabajo y no hay tiempo para el juego hará que las ardillitas sobrepasen sus límites?

added.title: El Onceavo Alienigena Parte 2
added.description: Ben descubre que Vilgax se ha unido a los Weatherheads para obligarlo a entregar el Omnitrix. Ahora no solo deberá superar sus dudas, sino también aceptar sus nuevos poderes, si es que quiere derrotar a sus enemigos.

added.title: Cazarecompensas
added.description: Mientras Gwen escucha una conferencia sobre el Ferrocarril Transcontinental, Ben se escapa en secreto a la tienda de regalos. Pero una vez que los Cazarrecompensas aparecen y acorralan a nuestro héroe, Gwen debe transmitir la información que aprendió en el tren y utilizarla para ayudar a Ben a escapar.

added.title: Los Supervillanso se Unen
added.description: Después de una pausa en las payasadas alienígenas, un inquieto Ben les sugiere a Max y Gwen que podría ser un mejor héroe si fuera solo. Pero cuando Vilgax consigue la ayuda de Zombozo para construir un mecanismo hipnotizador gigante para hipnotizar al mundo entero, Ben debe replantearse su estrategia si quiere derrotar al equipo de supervillanos.

added.title: Nuggets de Pollo de Sabiduria
added.description: Cuando Ben y Max comienzan a discutir, Ben se convierte en Fuego para desahogarse, contra la voluntad de Max. Pero una vez que el Dr. Animo lo ve y convierte a Max en un pollo, Ben debe enmendar su error si quiere salvar a su Abuelo y detener al Dr. Animo.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 1
added.description: Dan conoce a su pareja Bakugan, Drago, por primera vez y nos enteramos del "incidente" que ocurrió en la Tierra hace doce años.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 2
added.description: Dan y sus amigos ganan la Batalla Bakugan, demostrando que los Fantásticos son nuestros héroes y los mejores Peleadores Bakugan.

added.title: La Traes
added.description: Un despiadado juego de persecución desata un caos en el Arroyo, y se declara a Kelsey como la próxima perseguidora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Propinas
added.description: Luego de destruir por accidente el boleto de Falafel para un concierto, Manzana y Cebollín deben descubrir un modo de evitar la furia de Falafel.

added.title: Un Almuerzo Inesperado
added.description: Cuando el Restaurante de Hamburguesas es amenazado por un violento Bakugan, Dan llega para salvar el día...y las hamburguesas.

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Money Broom Wizard
added.description: Can Clarence, Jeff and Sumo manage to have a good time at "Pizza Swamp" Arcade with only one dollar to spend between them? Yes.

added.title: Una Leccion para Todos
added.description: Los Fantásticos le enseñan a unos chicos del vecindario a no imitar a los demás. Por ejemplo, a quienes utilizan a sus Bakugan con fines frívolos.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Lost in the Supermarket
added.description: During a trip to the supermarket with his mom, Clarence discovers produce adventure and coupon intrigue in aisle five...and every other aisle.

added.title: El Bravucon
added.description: Los Fantásticos deben lidiar con un bravucón que usa a su Bakugan para intimidar a los chicos del vecindario.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Bromas Pesadas
added.description: Las constantes bromas pesadas de Wynton colman la paciencia de su Bakugan, Trox, quien decide darle una lección.

added.title: Heroes Locales
added.description: Los Fantásticos provocan una ola de destrucción por accidente, y los padres de Dan se preguntan si deberían permitirle a los niños conservar sus Bakugan.

added.title: Pegatrix
added.description: Lia no concuerda con las técnicas de Pegatrix, pero durante una intensa batalla, debe aprender a confiar en los conocimientos de su Bakugan.

added.title: Caos en la cocina
added.description: Después de lesionarse en su lugar de trabajo, Richard no puede hacer sus tareas de criado. Unikitty y los demás se encargan de una simple tarea: limpiar la cocina. Esta actividad increíblemente aburrida es un desafío para nuestros héroes, que buscan todas las formas posibles de no hacerla. ¿Serán capaces de alcanzar esta meta y traer de regreso a Richard?

added.title: Ene-Amigos
added.description: Dos nuevos Peleadores Bakugan, Shun y Magnus, buscan ser parte de Los Fantásticos.

added.title: El Miedo de Strata
added.description: Los Fantásticos resuelven la misteriosa desaparición del Bakugan de un niño, y conocen a un cazador de Bakugan llamado Strata.

added.title: Perro Decisivo
added.description: Incapaz de tomar decisiones difíciles, Craig decide poner sus decisiones en manos de un perro llamado Fred.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Saca tu Bestia
added.description: Craig quiere jugar a un popular juego de cartas, así que decide tomar prestadas las cartas antiguas y valiosas de Bernard.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Bobbie Not Blobby
added.description: Axel discovers that the culprit behind Bobbie Blobby's missing mech-suit is Masko, who only wanted to clean out its clogged clay cannons, but lets the suit fall into the hands (or tentacles) of Dr. Nautilus - intent on flooding the sewers!

added.title: Sand Trap
added.description: Axel and the team take to the desert dunes of a playground sandbox as Madcap attempts to unearth an army of Spy Lizards from the same line as Galileo!

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Mystery Noise
added.description: It's Sleepover Dream Night in the RV and the gang just wants to get some sleep to dream their dreams, but when a mysterious noise keeps them awake, their grip on sanity begins slipping.

added.title: Viral Spiral
